{"headline": "New Study Shows How Exercise Impacts Muscle Recovery in Middle-Aged Adults",
"body": "A recent study compared the recovery response from high-volume resistance exercise between young and middle-aged adults. The study found no differences in the recovery response between the two age groups, suggesting that participating in recreational resistance training may mitigate any decline in muscle function during middle age. The study also noted similar patterns of muscle damage and inflammation between the groups. These findings highlight the importance of regular exercise for maintaining muscle health as we age.",
